main event: On 16th June 1953 at 2:0300Z in Alaska, an unidentified flying object was observed heading north at 13,500 ft, displaying various colors and disappearing after 10 minutes.
interesting points: The UFO was described as bright red to blue to bright white, displaying a colorful transformation.
The object was sighted at 2738Z Zulu and disappeared at 2748Z Zulu.
The report was initially misinterpreted as a circus message before being nullified by the 15th Air Division (Defense) Alaska.
There were no photographs or physical evidence of the UFO.
The conclusion stated 'insufficient data for evaluation' and follow-up information was not received.
